Consider the following C function:
int fun(int n) {
    int i, j;
    for (i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        for (j = 1; j < n; j += i) {
            printf("%d %d", i, j);
        }
    }
}
Time complexity of fun in terms of Theta notation is
A. Theta(n^2)
B. Theta(n^2 / log n)
C. Theta(n log n)
D. Theta(n * sqrt(n))

